cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category as it deals with security threats and privacy leakages targeting smartphones. It could also belong to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as it presents a framework for user authentication based on touch and movement behavior biometrics. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it addresses privacy concerns related to smartphone usage. The paper also involves the use of sensor data, which could place it under cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
